# 16. Cloud shadows

Even a simple cloud layer becomes much more convincing if it casts moving ground shadows.

Create a low-frequency cloud-shadow texture sampled in world space by the terrain material:

```wgsl
let shadow_uv =
    world_position.xz * cloud_scale
    + wind_offset;

let cloud_shadow =
    textureSample(
        cloud_shadow_texture,
        cloud_sampler,
        shadow_uv,
    ).r;

direct_light *= mix(
    1.0,
    cloud_shadow_min,
    cloud_shadow * cloud_coverage,
);
```

Apply the same attenuation to vegetation materials.

This does not have to be a literal Bevy shadow map. A shared material uniform or texture works well and is cheaper.

