# 24. Suggested initial settings

For a Windows RTX 3070 vertical slice:

## Enable

* Procedural atmosphere.
* One sun directional light.
* Atmosphere environment lighting.
* Cascaded sun shadows.
* HDR.
* Tonemapping.
* Distance fog.
* Bloom at low strength.
* SSAO.
* TAA if compatible with your motion and foliage.
* One simple cloud layer.
* Local fog volumes only in showcase regions.

## Delay

* Full volumetric clouds.
* Two shadow-casting celestial lights.
* Extensive shadow-casting grass.
* Many shadowed point lights.
* Large-scale real-time global illumination.
* Per-frame environment-map regeneration at high resolution.
* Dense volumetric fog over the entire island.

---

# 25. Performance priorities

The most expensive systems are likely to be:

1. Directional shadow rendering.
2. Dense vegetation overdraw.
3. Volumetric fog.
4. Volumetric clouds.
5. Screen-space effects.
6. Many shadowed local lights.
7. Water reflection passes.

Profile them together. Each system may run well alone but exceed the budget when combined.

Suggested quality tiers:

| Feature           | Low              | Medium                   | High                       |
| ----------------- | ---------------- | ------------------------ | -------------------------- |
| Atmosphere        | standard         | standard                 | raymarched/high quality    |
| Sun shadows       | short range      | 3–4 cascades             | long range/high resolution |
| Fog               | distance only    | distance + local volumes | dense volumetric           |
| Clouds            | textured layer   | raymarched layer         | full volumetric            |
| Contact shadows   | off              | characters only          | broad nearby use           |
| SSAO              | low              | medium                   | high                       |
| Water reflections | environment only | SSR                      | planar/hybrid              |
| Local shadows     | hero only        | selected                 | broad use                  |

