# Final recommendation

For your project, use this initial stack:

```text
Camera
├── Atmosphere
├── AtmosphereEnvironmentMapLight
├── HDR
├── Exposure
├── Tonemapping
├── DistanceFog
└── optional VolumetricFog

Sun entity
├── DirectionalLight
├── CascadeShadowConfig
└── VolumetricLight where needed

Moon entity
└── secondary DirectionalLight, active mainly at night

World
├── simple animated cloud layer
├── local FogVolumes
├── reflection-aware water
└── biome/weather-driven lighting profiles
```

The key design decision is to let **one shared celestial and weather state drive every visual system**. The atmosphere, directional light, environment map, fog, clouds, grass, terrain and water should never calculate independent versions of daylight.

